# Model Guidance

Cursor does not switch models mid-session automatically — this is advisory
for you (the developer) when picking a model per chat/mode, not something an
agent can enforce on itself. Use it as a rule of thumb, not a hard gate.

## By complexity (from solve-ticket's classification)

- **SIMPLE** — fast/cheap model is usually enough. Pattern-following, 1
  file, no new decisions.
- **STANDARD** — mid-tier "balanced" model. Cross-component work, needs to
  verify existing patterns before extending them.
- **COMPLEX** — strongest available reasoning model. New patterns,
  cross-cutting, multi-layer impact — this is where a wrong architectural
  call is expensive to unwind later.

## By phase, if planning/implementation are split

Applies whenever a ticket auto-splits (`solve-ticket`'s Phase 2.5, any
STANDARD/COMPLEX ticket) or you invoke `plan-ticket` /
`Implement [TICKET-ID]` manually:

- **Planning pass** — favor a stronger reasoning model even for
  STANDARD-complexity tickets. Mistakes here (wrong API contract, missed
  constraint) propagate into every later step and are expensive to catch
  after implementation has started.
- **Implementation pass** — the plan file already carries the hard
  decisions, so a faster/cheaper model can often execute it — bump up only
  if the plan itself flags open questions or the ticket is COMPLEX.
- **Retrospective / PR description** — cheapest model available. Low risk,
  low reasoning depth, mostly summarization.

## Signals to override the default upward, regardless of complexity

- Auth, payments, or PII touched anywhere in the diff.
- Ticket references a prior incident or "intermittent"/"flaky" symptom
  (usually concurrency — needs deeper reasoning than the file count suggests).
- You're already on a second failed attempt at the same fix (see the
  Circuit Breaker rule in `project-rules.mdc`) — escalate model tier before
  trying a third time, not after.

## Keeping instruction files in sync

This project maintains AI coding assistant instructions in three places:

- **VS Code / GitHub Copilot**: `.github/instructions/*.instructions.md`
- **Cursor**: `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
- **Claude Code**: `CLAUDE.md`

When modifying any instruction file, apply the same change to all three locations so they stay consistent.
